  "title": "Finance Controller, Single Family Office",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Summary</strong></u>:<br />Ensures accurate books and records to support business decisions, and for statutory reporting, and managing operations and accounting as information repository for Family Office. <br /><br /><strong>Work Activities</strong>   <br /><br /><em><strong>Review of operation + Report generation</strong></em></p><ul><li>Review payment lists and expense records (in excel templates)</li><li>Upload records to accounting system </li><li>Bank reconciliation for expense and cash balances against reports in accounting system </li><li>Maintain records in accounting system</li><li>Generating various expense report, Expense budget variance reports, Cashflow reports, weekly cash reports</li></ul><p><em><strong>Accounting for financial, tax and statutory reporting</strong></em></p><ul><li>Preparing financial statements for entities and for consolidated Family Office</li><li>Preparing GST assessments for payments to/refunds from IRAS</li><li>Preparing tax information and reports for tax reporting</li><li>Preparing financials for statutory reports</li><li>Ensure that all statutory and internal deadlines are met for reporting purposes. </li><li>Assisting with yearly budget forecast and periodic budget updates. </li></ul><p>  <em><strong>Collaboration with other parties</strong></em></p><ul><li>Meeting info requests</li><li>Managing and reviewing operations processes as part of internal controls</li><li>Liaise with tax agents and external service providers</li></ul><p><u><strong>Qualifications and skills</strong></u></p><ul><li>Experience from Big 4 accounting firms, fund service provider, or in-house finance department</li><li>Bachelor in Accounting</li><li>Good communication and interpersonal skills to liaise with different parties</li><li>Well versed using MS Office and accounting systems</li></ul>",
